[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "6. The Linares Variation"]
[Black "The Linares Variation #3: White argues he has the better endgame"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 Nf6 5. e4 b5 6. Nxb5 Qa5+ 7. Nc3 Nxe4 8.
Qa4+ { White wants to argue that the endgame is good for him... he is wrong. }
8... Qxa4 9. Nxa4 Nd6
{ Not a simple move. We cannot hold onto both pawns. It was never our intention but holding onto the c4-pawn will disrupt White the most. }
10. Nxc5 g6
{ We proceed with our normal development in all the lines of the Linares variation. }
11. Bf4 Bg7 12. O-O-O { White defends the b-pawn. } 12... Na6
{ Forcing the exchange and thus giving us some more development. Black is clearly better. }
*

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "6. The Linares Variation"]
[Black "The Linares Variation #4: The give that back line with 9. fxe7"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. Nc3 c5 4. d5 Nf6 5. e4 b5 6. e5
{ This is the move you will meet more often than not. } 6... b4
{ Counter-attacking. } 7. exf6 bxc3
{ Look at those queenside pawns. Our opponents will think we are crazy, but Black's position is actually quite good. }
8. bxc3
{ This is forced. If  8.Bxc4  cxb2  9.Bxb2  Qa5+  10.Qd2  Qxd2+  11.Kxd2  exf6  Black is clearly better. }
8... Nd7 9. fxe7 { This is wrong but is played the most often. } 9... Bxe7 10.
Bxc4 O-O 11. Nf3
{ This is an important move. White could play  11.Nge2  protecting c3 and closing the e-file. Then Black should concentrate on winning back the d-pawn:  11...Nb6  12.Bd3   or  12.Bb3  c4  13.Bc2  Qxd5  12...Qxd5. }
11... Bf6 12. Qd3 { 12.Bd2  Re8+  13.Be2  Ba6! } 12... Nb6
{ By defending with the queen he has the option of playing Be3 so we do not give a check on the e-file. }
13. O-O { Getting his king to safety and getting the rook to come and defend. }
13... Nxc4 14. Qxc4 { White cannot hold the c3 pawn and the d5 pawn. } 14...
Qa5
{ Threatening Ba6 and Qxc3. Black is better because he will regain the pawn and have the two bishop advantage. }
*

