[Black "The grinding endgames #2: The inferior Open Endgame"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 c5 { We play our normal move. } 4. Nf3
{ 4.d5  transposes to the Linares variation. } 4... cxd4
{ This leads to the 'open endgame'. } 5. Nxd4 { This is inferior. } 5... e5 6.
Nb5 a6 { Now White will exchange queens which allows our King to protect c7. }
7. Qxd8+ Kxd8 { Now White has to retreat. } 8. N5c3 Be6 { Black is better. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "8. The Grinding Endgames"]
[Black "The grinding endgames #3: The Open Endgame"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e4 c5 4. Nf3 cxd4 5. Qxd4
{ This leads to the Open Endgame. } 5... Qxd4 6. Nxd4 Bd7
{ 6...a6  is also playable. We have to cover b5 square. } 7. Bxc4 Nc6 8. Nxc6
Bxc6 { This position has been seen in a number of 'Grandmaster Draws'. } 9. Nc3
e6 10. Be3 a6 { freeing the Rook. } 11. f3
{ Defending e4 and making a square on f2 for the King. } 11... Nf6 12. Kf2 Nd7
{ The idea is to play Bc5 to exchange some pieces. } 13. Rhd1 Bc5 14. Rd2
{ Taking on c5 does not promise any more of an advantage. } 14... Bxe3+ 15.
Kxe3 g5
{ It is Black now that starts to attack. At the right time Ne5 will come. } *

[Event "?"]
[Site "?"]
[Date "????.??.??"]
[Round "?"]
[White "8. The Grinding Endgames"]
[Black "The grinding endgames #4: The boring clasical endgame"]
[Result "*"]

1. d4 d5 2. c4 dxc4 3. e3 c5 4. Bxc4 e6 5. Nf3 Nf6 6. O-O a6 7. dxc5
{ White declares he is boring and wants a boring endgame. } 7... Bxc5
{ Caruana has shown that this is the best way to proceed. We now intend to castle short and therefore White has to exchange queens immediately if he wants to keep a tiny initiative. }
8. Qxd8+ Kxd8
{ This wins half a tempo because White will at some stage play Rd1+. } 9. Nbd2
Ke7 { This is the natural home of our king in these endgames. } 10. b3
{ White has many different development plans. Our development will be as follows: }
10... Rd8 11. Bb2 b6
{ 11...b5  is possible but then a2-a4 may become an issue. } 12. Rfd1 Bb7 13.
Rac1 Nbd7
{ If given the chance we shall try to attack on the king side with Ne5 and/ or g5. }
